         <div type="translation">
            <pb xml:id="tr-1r" n="1r" facs="#i1"/>
            <p>…And our Prince, this David, also stipulated that, if, God forbid, this Nāšiyya shall
               die without offspring, half of this dowry should be returned to her father’s house
               according to the custom of the children of the Land of Israel and … moreover he
               agreed not to force this Nāšiyya, his wife, to sit with him in the light of the
               Sabbath, nor to eat the fat (of the sheep’s) tail, nor to profane her own festivals,
               on condition that she observe with him the festivals … And we have carried out an act
               of acquisition from the honourable, great, holy, our master and teacher, our Prince,
               this David the Prince, Prince of the Exile of all Israel, son of the honourable,
               great, holy, our master and teacher, our lord, our Prince, Daniel the [great] Prince,
               Head of the Academy of the ‘Pride of Jacob’ – may his sacred memory be for a blessing
               – for this Nāšiyya, a young woman, this virgin bride, daughter of the honourable,
               great, holy, our master and teacher, our lord, our noble, Moses ha-Kohen, Banner of
               the Jews, their Stronghold, and the Joy of [their Crown, with an implement suitable
               for] acquisition, regarding all that is written and explained above. Fit and
               established.</p>
            <pb xml:id="tr-1v" n="1v" facs="#i2"/>
         </div>
